env.#desc: Manages the Environment Variables for your current Project

inspect.#desc: Displays information related to a deployment

link.#desc: Link local directory to a Vercel Project

login.#desc: Logs into your account or creates a new one

pull.#desc: Pull your Project Settings from the cloud

switch.#desc: Switches between teams and your personal account

bisect.#desc: Use binary search to find the deployment that introduced a bug

secrets.#desc: Manages your global Secrets, for use in Environment Variables

logs.#desc: Displays the logs for a deployment

whoami.#desc: Shows the username of the currently logged in user

-V|--platform-version.#desc: Set the platform version to deploy to

-f|--force.#desc: Force a new deployment even if nothing has changed

-e|--env.#desc: Include an env var during run time (e.g.: \`-e KEY=value\`). Can appear many times.

-b|--build-env.#desc: Similar to \`--env\` but for build time only.

-m|--meta.#desc: Add metadata for the deployment (e.g.: \`-m KEY=value\`). Can appear many times.

-C|--no-clipboard.#desc: Do not attempt to copy URL to clipboard

--regions.#desc: Set default regions to enable the deployment on

-c|--confirm.#desc: Confirm default options and skip questions
